<h2>Youth Summer Camp 2012</h2><p class="eventtime">Monday, July 30, 2012 - Friday, August 03, 2012</p><br/><b>Group:</b> Middle School Ministry, High School Ministry</p><div id="text"><h3>Camp Theme: "Line In The Sand"</h3>
<p><strong>A Definition:</strong> A point of decision; a point beyond which there is a new reality; a point of no return.</p>
<p>Calling all Middle School &ndash; High School students from around Oregon and Southern Washington to join us at Twin Rocks Friends Camp for an unforgettable summer camp experience! This camp is one the West Coast&rsquo;s most scenic camps right on the beautiful Oregon coast beach with awesome lake activities, a massive new indoor gym, and many other options. This camp has it all!</p>
<p>"Line in the Sand" Summer Camp offers every student the chance to draw "a line in the sand" of your life, and then to leap over it! Not only will there be plenty of fun, but Line in the Sand is set up to be just that: a point of growth and decision in the life of every student. From services that will include impactful worship and moving messages, to small group discussions and personal reflection time, this camp offers each student the opportunity to pause, focus on what their life is all about, and make decisions to reaffirm or redirect the &ldquo;next steps&rdquo; of their life.</p>
<h3>Camp Activities</h3>
<p>Disc golf, swimming, boating, fishing, hiking, miniature golf, horseshoes, group competitions and plenty of free time!&nbsp; The camp also has a newly renovated gymnasium that provides basketball, volleyball, ping-pong, foosball, billiards, air hockey and shuffleboard.&nbsp;</p>
<h3>What to Bring</h3>
<p>Toiletries, Towel, Toothbrush, Toothpaste, Clothes for service and activities, Bathing Suit, Comb, Brush, Deodorant and Soap!! Sleeping Bag, Pillow, Bible, Notepad, Pen and an Expectancy to see God move in your life and your Youth Group.</p>
<h3>What NOT to Bring</h3>
<p>NO drugs, cigarettes, alcohol, fireworks, matches, firearms, knives, portable music, DVD, or game devices (iPods etc).</p>
